<h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold mb-8">About</h1>

<div class="space-y-10 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">

  {# ── Mission ────────────────────────────────────────── #}
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-3">The Mission</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p>
        Nashville has a growing Irish traditional music community, but finding out what gets played at sessions — and where to find the dots — has always been word-of-mouth at best. This site is an attempt to change that.
      </p>
      <p>
        We keep a best-effort record of what was played at local sessions: the tunes, the keys, the sets, and links to sheet music and recordings on <a href="https://thesession.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">TheSession.org</a>. Think of it as a living tunebook for Nashville's folk music scene.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether you're a regular looking to practice what we played last week, a newcomer figuring out what to learn first, or just curious about the local tradition — this is for you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {# ── Divider ────────────────────────────────────────── #}
  <hr class="border-border">

  {# ── The Humans ─────────────────────────────────────── #}
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-6">The Humans (& Non-Humans)</h2>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      {# KJ #}
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent-dim border border-border flex items-center justify-center text-lg flex-shrink-0">🎻</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold mb-1">KJ Krause</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-2">Fiddler · Session regular · Curator</p>
          <p>
            KJ started attending Nashville's Irish sessions and quickly realized there was no good way to share what got played each week. He'd been keeping tunelists on Notion — painstakingly linking each set to sheet music on TheSession — but figured the community deserved something better than a private page behind a share link.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            So he built this site. Or rather, he and Slime built it together.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {# Slime #}
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent-dim border border-border flex items-center justify-center text-lg flex-shrink-0">🫠</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold mb-1">Slime</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-2">Non-Newtonian intelligence · Co-builder</p>
          <p>
            Slime is KJ's AI assistant — a <a href="https://openclaw.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">OpenClaw</a>-powered agent that helps with everything from scraping tune data off TheSession to building and deploying this site. Think of Slime as the tireless intern who actually enjoys cross-referencing ABC notation at 2am.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Every tune ID, setting link, and key on this site was sourced and verified through TheSession's API — Slime handles the plumbing so KJ can focus on playing.
