  {# ── How It Works ───────────────────────────────────── #}
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mb-3">How It Works</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p>
        After each session, KJ jots down the sets and tunes as best he can remember. Slime then enriches that data — looking up each tune on <a href="https://thesession.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">TheSession.org</a>, finding the right settings (specific transcriptions), and linking everything together.
      </p>
      <p>
        The result is a structured record where every tune links to its sheet music and every set links back to its source. The data lives in simple JSON files, the site is built with <a href="https://www.11ty.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">Eleventy</a>, and it's all <a href="https://github.com/kocopelly/nashville-folk-session" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">open source</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

